.TH "queue_qp_for_tid_wait" 9 "queue_qp_for_tid_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
queue_qp_for_tid_wait \- suspend QP on tid space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" queue_qp_for_tid_wait
.BI "(struct hfi1_ctxtdata *rcd "  ","
.BI "struct tid_queue *queue "  ","
.BI "struct rvt_qp *qp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rcd" 12
the receive context
.IP "queue" 12
the queue to operate on
.IP "qp" 12
the qp
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The qp is inserted at the tail of the rcd
wait queue and the HFI1_S_WAIT_TID_SPACE s_flag is set.

Must hold the qp s_lock and the exp_lock.
